sudo apt install python3 python3-pip 

sudo apt install python3-django (or) python -m pip3 install django
django-admin --version (or) python -m django --version

pip3 install flake8
(python library that wraps PyFlakes + PEP8 + pycodestyle)
(the best Logical & Stylistic linter for python)
(better than pylint and pep8)

(Ctrl+Shift+P) and select the Python: Select Linter 
Choose Flake8

Add these to settings.json of vscode
(path => ~/home/wc/.config/Code/User/{}settings.json)

{
    "python.linting.flake8Args": [
        "--max-line-length=120",
        "--ignore=E302,E305, E501",
		 //ignoring line too long error flake8(E501) 
    ],
}

After installing django extension in vscode, settings.json must be updated by adding "emmet.includeLanguages":{} to track both django and html extensions in .html files.

{
    "editor.fontSize": 18,
    "editor.fontWeight": "bold",
    "editor.cursorStyle": "block",
    "editor.cursorBlinking": "expand",
    "workbench.iconTheme": "vscode-icons",
    "sync.gist": "",
    "workbench.colorTheme": "Visual Studio Dark",
    "editor.renderWhitespace": "all",
    "editor.minimap.enabled": false,
    "window.menuBarVisibility": "toggle",
    "[django-html]": {
        
    },
    "emmet.includeLanguages": {
        "django-html": "html"
    },
    "python.linting.flake8Args": [
        "--max-line-length=120",
        "--ignore=E302,E305, E501",
    ],
}




